# .trivyignore — unfixable OS-level CVEs with justifications
# All entries have Status "affected" or "fix_deferred" with no fixed version
# available in Debian 13 (Trixie) as of 2026-06-24.
# Reviewed and accepted as risk for demo environment.
# Production action: monitor Debian security tracker and patch when fixes release.
# Tracker: https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/

# ncurses — CVE-2025-69720
# Buffer overflow in ncurses. No fixed version in Debian 13.
# ncurses is an essential base package, cannot be removed.
# Low exploitability — terminal library, not directly exposed via network.
CVE-2025-69720

# SQLite — CVE-2026-11822, CVE-2026-11824
# Memory corruption in SQLite. No fixed version in Debian 13.
# Bundled with Python, cannot be independently upgraded.
# Not directly used by this application.
CVE-2026-11822
CVE-2026-11824

# perl-base — multiple CVEs
# perl-base is an essential Debian package and cannot be removed
# (apt requires --allow-remove-essential which risks breaking the image).
# These CVEs are in Archive::Tar and IO::Compress — not used by this app.
# No fixed version available in Debian 13 for most of these.
CVE-2026-42496
CVE-2026-42497
CVE-2026-8376
CVE-2026-48962
CVE-2026-9538

# setuptools vendored packages (base image)
# python:3.11-slim ships with setuptools-79.0.1 which vendors old
# versions of jaraco.context and wheel containing these CVEs.
# We install setuptools-80.9.0 on top but the base image version
# cannot be removed as it's part of the Python base layer.
# Our application code does not invoke these vendored packages.
CVE-2026-23949
CVE-2026-24049
